":236,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Death: Do not speak evil about the deceased","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 15, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen your companion dies, leave him alone and do not malign him.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4899 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u062a\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0627\u062d\u0650\u0628\u064f\u0643\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0641\u064e\u062f\u064e\u0639\u064f\u0648\u0647\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":105,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/11\/08\/warning-lies-jokes\/","url_meta":{"origin":236,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Joking: Warning not to tell a lie, even as a joke","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 8, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Mu'awiyyah ibn Haydah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWoe to one who tells lies to make people laugh. Woe to him! Woe to him!\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4990 Grade:\u00a0Hasan (fair) according to Al-Arna'ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u0639\u0627\u0648\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u062d\u064a\u062f\u0629 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":43244,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/18\/helps-fellow-travelers\/","url_meta":{"origin":236,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Travel: The Prophet helps his fellow travelers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 18, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn \u2018Abdillah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would stay behind the caravan, encouraging the weak to catch up, letting them ride with him, and supplicating for them. Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 2639 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15326,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/23\/sahaba-awe-prophet-sitting\/","url_meta":{"origin":236,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Sitting: Companions in awe of the Prophet","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Qaylah bint Makhramah reported: I saw the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, sitting with his arms around his legs. When I saw the Messenger of Allah sitting so humbly, I trembled in awe of him. Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4847 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Arna'ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0629\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5423,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/20\/adab-children-elders\/","url_meta":{"origin":236,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Manners: Respectful to elders, merciful to children","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 20, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever does not show mercy to our young ones, or acknowledge the rights of our elders, he is not one of us.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4943 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Arna'ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34507,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/10\/21\/best-sadaqah-little-available\/","url_meta":{"origin":236,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Sadaqah: Best charity is given when little is available","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 21, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: He said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, which charity is best?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cOne with little property to give. Begin with your dependents.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 1677 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/236","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=236"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/236\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=236"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=236"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=236"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}